WEBVTT

00:53.688 --> 00:55.922
And they lived happily...

00:55.924 --> 00:58.423
- Ever after!
- Ever after!

01:11.171 --> 01:13.773
Shema Israel?

01:13.775 --> 01:17.677
<i>Shema Israel, Hashem Eloheinu,
Hashem Echad.</i>

01:17.679 --> 01:19.879
- Amen.
- Amen.

01:19.881 --> 01:21.581
Love you.

01:21.583 --> 01:24.418
Love you, too. Goodnight.

01:33.661 --> 01:36.396
- Father...
- Mh-hm?

01:40.167 --> 01:42.102
Why do they hate us?

01:44.939 --> 01:48.841
I don't think they hate us.

01:48.843 --> 01:51.142
Hitler is just blaming us
for the suffering

01:51.144 --> 01:52.979
of the working class

01:52.981 --> 01:55.115
and some people
choose to believe him.

01:57.184 --> 01:59.119
But why?

02:01.121 --> 02:02.890
It's not a simple
answer...

02:04.626 --> 02:07.660
...but I can tell you this..

02:07.662 --> 02:09.494
The economy is getting better.

02:09.496 --> 02:12.798
And soon they will stop focusing
on who to blame

02:12.800 --> 02:16.167
for what didn't work,
and everyone will set their eyes

02:16.169 --> 02:18.537
on building a better future.

02:18.539 --> 02:20.539
We just have to keep
contributing our part

02:20.541 --> 02:25.443
to Germany,
like we have always done.

02:25.445 --> 02:27.379
Go to sleep now.

02:27.381 --> 02:29.782
You have school tomorrow,
and you are too young

02:29.784 --> 02:31.653
<i>to worry about
these things, hm.</i>

02:36.024 --> 02:38.693
- Love you.
- I love you, too.

05:08.142 --> 05:09.644
<i>Ten-hut!</i>

05:12.213 --> 05:13.681
General Patton.

05:29.564 --> 05:31.362
Good evening, soldiers!

05:31.364 --> 05:33.000
Good evening, sir!

05:34.602 --> 05:36.336
At ease!

05:39.540 --> 05:42.975
If we take the generally
accepted definition of bravery

05:42.977 --> 05:46.979
as a quality which knows no fear

05:46.981 --> 05:50.683
I have never seen a brave man.

05:50.685 --> 05:54.485
All men are frightened.

05:54.487 --> 05:57.656
Courage is no more than fear

05:57.658 --> 06:01.260
holding on a minute longer.

06:01.262 --> 06:06.065
Now imagine fighting this war
as a civilian.

06:06.067 --> 06:08.801
Imagine not knowing
how to shoot a gun

06:08.803 --> 06:13.174
and challenging the Nazis
to save lives.

06:16.010 --> 06:20.145
I've just heard
an incredible story.

06:20.147 --> 06:22.548
I'd like to share it with you.

06:22.550 --> 06:25.450
<i>Because it's a story</i>

06:25.452 --> 06:28.854
about one of those unique
human beings

06:28.856 --> 06:31.924
that makes your sacrifices

06:31.926 --> 06:34.693
and your heroism

06:34.695 --> 06:36.831
completely worth it.

07:34.855 --> 07:37.959
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

07:39.360 --> 07:41.492
Oh, my God! Father!
What a surprise to see you!

07:41.494 --> 07:43.829
How dare you?

07:43.831 --> 07:45.297
Did you like my show?

07:45.299 --> 07:48.133
You are a clown dressed like
Hitler in a whorehouse..

07:48.135 --> 07:52.171
Papa, it's not Hitler, it's
Chaplin and it's a cabaret..

07:52.173 --> 07:54.308
Oh, I apologize
for my confusion.

07:55.609 --> 07:58.546
Father, I'm an actor.

08:00.781 --> 08:02.917
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

08:07.021 --> 08:11.392
We have to start early tomorrow.
Let's go home. Go.

08:21.135 --> 08:24.005
Mrs. Garber is coming.
Mrs. Garber is coming.

08:26.140 --> 08:29.541
- Hello, Mrs. Garber.
- Hello.

08:29.543 --> 08:33.445
- How is Emma?
- She's good, thank you.

08:33.447 --> 08:35.581
How come you always
ask about her?

08:35.583 --> 08:39.184
Actually, my father wants me
to marry her.

08:39.186 --> 08:41.322
- Really?
- Really.

08:42.790 --> 08:44.890
Is that true, Charles?

08:44.892 --> 08:47.092
Is she Jewish?

08:47.094 --> 08:49.528
- I think so.
- Then, no.

08:49.530 --> 08:50.865
Why?

08:52.466 --> 08:54.299
I wouldn't wish on
any Jewish girl

08:54.301 --> 08:57.436
the infinite disgrace of dealing
for life with this useless bum

08:57.438 --> 09:00.574
who wants to be a clown
and has the muscles of a ghost.

09:04.011 --> 09:05.512
Well, most of that is true.

09:05.514 --> 09:08.047
Emma is the only Jewish woman
in the world

09:08.049 --> 09:09.982
who doesn't want to marry.

09:09.984 --> 09:12.119
You shouldn't waste your time.

09:13.988 --> 09:16.123
Thank you.

09:23.597 --> 09:27.900
- I don't think that worked.
- No, I think it did.

09:27.902 --> 09:30.235
- She now thinks you are a bum.
- No, no.

09:30.237 --> 09:32.971
Psychological projection,
according to Dr. Freud.

09:32.973 --> 09:36.108
- Never heard of him.
- I know. Uh..

09:36.110 --> 09:38.877
Blaming others can lead to
a "kick the dog" effect

09:38.879 --> 09:40.212
where individuals in a hierarchy

09:40.214 --> 09:41.480
blame their immediate
subordinate

09:41.482 --> 09:43.182
and this propagates
down the chain

09:43.184 --> 09:45.319
until the lowest rung.

09:46.253 --> 09:47.786
What does that even mean?

09:47.788 --> 09:50.089
It means if the butcher thinks
you are a bum

09:50.091 --> 09:52.226
you are probably a genius.

09:53.961 --> 09:56.061
- Mh-hm!
- Yes.

09:56.063 --> 09:58.533
- Ah!
- Tell Dr. Freud to cure that!

10:02.369 --> 10:05.304
- Good evening, uncle.
- <i>Shalom,</i> Georges.

10:05.306 --> 10:08.541
Do you mind if I talk to Marcel
for a second?

10:08.543 --> 10:11.043
I've told you a million times,
I'm a serious actor, okay?

10:11.045 --> 10:12.579
I'm not a clown.

10:12.581 --> 10:15.214
I just need your help.
These kids went through a lot.

10:15.216 --> 10:17.116
What do I care
what they went through?

10:17.118 --> 10:18.585
- Don't say that.
- I'm saying it.

10:18.587 --> 10:20.219
I'm saying. I'm sorry,
I don't care, okay?

10:20.221 --> 10:21.487
I'm not good with children.

10:21.489 --> 10:23.222
You know, I have no patience.
Sorry.

10:23.224 --> 10:24.823
You know, I barely have time
to work with my father

10:24.825 --> 10:26.091
he now wants me there all day.

10:26.093 --> 10:27.493
I have an entire play
I'm working on

10:27.495 --> 10:29.094
where I interpret 30 different
characters.

10:29.096 --> 10:30.462
- Thirty!
- Marcel!

10:30.464 --> 10:33.098
- What?
- These are Jewish orphans.

10:33.100 --> 10:35.334
I know that. I know that.
You know, I.. sorry, I..

10:35.336 --> 10:37.302
I definitely have
an alive Jewish father.

10:37.304 --> 10:38.437
That hasn't made my life
any easier.

10:38.439 --> 10:40.575
That's a horrible thing to say.

10:42.676 --> 10:44.943
- How do you want me to help?
- Go work on your play.

10:44.945 --> 10:47.212
- Ah..
- You have many characters to write.

10:47.214 --> 10:49.047
- Georges!
- Go away.

10:49.049 --> 10:51.016
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

11:03.598 --> 11:06.331
Hi, Flore.

11:24.952 --> 11:27.520
I just saw your mother.

11:27.522 --> 11:31.356
She was telling my father
that I should marry you, hm.

11:31.358 --> 11:33.825
Strange. That generation,
I guess, they're old, you know.

11:33.827 --> 11:35.662
They don't understand that,
of course, we would only

11:35.664 --> 11:37.829
get married for love.

11:37.831 --> 11:41.366
And you couldn't find love
at the cabaret, could you?

11:41.368 --> 11:43.235
Hey, don't believe everything
you hear about that place.

11:43.237 --> 11:44.504
- Okay?
- I'm sure it's very reputable.

11:44.506 --> 11:45.804
Well, art can happen anywhere.

11:45.806 --> 11:49.241
Okay, look at, uh,
look at Marcel Duchamp.

11:49.243 --> 11:50.909
I don't know who that is.

11:50.911 --> 11:53.845
Yes, well, you should before you
judge an artist by his canvas.

11:53.847 --> 11:55.480
And your canvas is the cabaret?

11:55.482 --> 11:58.285
Yes. No. No, what?
Who are you again?

11:59.787 --> 12:02.221
- The girl you want to marry.
- Excuse me, no, no.

12:02.223 --> 12:03.455
I don't want to marry you.

12:03.457 --> 12:04.723
Your mother wants you
to marry me

12:04.725 --> 12:07.826
and I was just being polite
to her.

12:07.828 --> 12:09.596
There they are!

12:09.598 --> 12:13.801
- How many did you say?
- 123 children.

12:15.503 --> 12:19.204
<i>The foundation paid a fortune
for their lives.</i>

12:19.206 --> 12:22.343
<i>Their parents were just killed
by Nazis.</i>

12:31.785 --> 12:32.951
Marcel..

13:07.656 --> 13:09.591
You want to look?

13:21.969 --> 13:24.169
- Are you ready?
- I am.

13:24.171 --> 13:25.638
Why is my brother here?

13:25.640 --> 13:27.507
<i>I thought he may clown
for the kids.</i>

13:27.509 --> 13:29.509
He only cares about himself.

13:29.511 --> 13:32.647
And God forbid you call him
clown, he'll get all crazy.

13:34.148 --> 13:37.182
<i>Look, if he doesn't help,
we'll send him home</i>

13:37.184 --> 13:39.451
but at this point
we need everyone.

13:39.453 --> 13:43.188
Alright. That bus is not enough.

13:43.190 --> 13:44.892
<i>It's all we've got.</i>

13:46.393 --> 13:48.596
I can get our father's truck.

13:50.097 --> 13:52.232
That's a good idea.

13:53.601 --> 13:55.467
Make sure there's no knives
or meat in there.

13:55.469 --> 13:57.237
<i>The children are afraid.</i>

13:59.039 --> 14:00.238
Go.

14:12.587 --> 14:13.887
Alright.

14:19.126 --> 14:20.762
Come on. Let's go.

14:22.831 --> 14:24.766
What's wrong? Let's go.

14:33.675 --> 14:35.175
Hmm.

14:41.215 --> 14:43.115
Let's go.

14:54.228 --> 14:55.896
<i>Do you wanna come down?</i>

15:00.934 --> 15:04.871
This way. Careful.

15:04.873 --> 15:06.808
It's okay.

15:34.968 --> 15:36.435
Easy! Don't be this way.

15:37.906 --> 15:40.972
Oh, oh. Calm down.
Everybody, calm down. Calm down.

15:40.974 --> 15:44.009
Calm down. There is food
for everyone.

15:44.011 --> 15:45.645
There's no need to fight.

15:45.647 --> 15:48.480
Sit down at the table.
No, no need..

15:48.482 --> 15:50.415
- <i>I'll give you this..</i>
- <i>No pushing.</i>

15:50.417 --> 15:52.854
<i>Georges. Georges,
please help me.</i>

16:01.094 --> 16:03.030
Try this one.

16:05.399 --> 16:08.368
- Is it too big?
- No, it's fine.

16:20.013 --> 16:22.582
It's alright.

16:22.584 --> 16:25.283
You are becoming a big girl.

16:25.285 --> 16:27.520
Come with me.

16:27.522 --> 16:29.990
Mila, I'll be right back.

16:34.629 --> 16:36.764
Am I going to be okay?

16:43.203 --> 16:45.437
You are okay.

16:45.439 --> 16:48.641
This happens to every woman.

16:48.643 --> 16:51.142
It happens to me.

16:51.144 --> 16:53.080
It just means you are growing.

16:54.682 --> 16:59.785
So, from now on,
once a month for a few days

16:59.787 --> 17:03.221
you are going to have to wear
one of these.

17:03.223 --> 17:04.289
What's that?

17:04.291 --> 17:05.858
It's a special napkin

17:05.860 --> 17:09.629
that makes sure the blood
doesn't reach your clothes.

17:09.631 --> 17:12.598
It's only going to last
for a few days.

17:12.600 --> 17:16.536
It's like, um, a rehearsal
to prepare for the day

17:16.538 --> 17:21.039
<i>many years from now, when you
are ready to have a baby.</i>

17:21.041 --> 17:27.145
No. No running. No, no.
There is no need to run.

17:27.147 --> 17:29.180
You're gonna hurt yourself.

17:41.328 --> 17:43.428
Calm down everyone.

17:43.430 --> 17:45.998
Please, no standing
on the table.

17:46.000 --> 17:49.167
Be nice to each other.
You're family now.

17:49.169 --> 17:51.773
This is your new home.

19:04.378 --> 19:06.514
What's he doing?

20:55.990 --> 20:59.160
Wait, wait, wait, wait. Blow!

21:56.316 --> 21:57.752
Blow.

22:07.094 --> 22:08.229
Go.

23:30.044 --> 23:34.181
You dress like a clown,
you paint a clown.

23:39.921 --> 23:42.056
What can I do for you?

23:48.162 --> 23:52.465
You rub the brush on paint,
you draw a face.

23:54.302 --> 23:58.804
I'm not going to say it's ugly,
I think you are getting better.

23:58.806 --> 24:01.607
<i>I just never quiet understood
why does anyone do it</i>

24:01.609 --> 24:03.542
even when it's great.

24:03.544 --> 24:05.478
Tell me. Why do you do it?

24:08.616 --> 24:10.481
Why do you go to the bathroom?

24:10.483 --> 24:12.418
Oh, you need not
to offend your father.

24:12.420 --> 24:14.485
No, no.
No, I'm not offending you.

24:14.487 --> 24:18.359
I'm, I'm asking.
Why do you go to the bathroom?

24:19.994 --> 24:23.130
Because my body
gives me no choice.

24:25.833 --> 24:27.933
There it is.

24:27.935 --> 24:30.071
That's my answer
to your question.

25:13.781 --> 25:15.381
- Amen.
- Amen.

25:15.383 --> 25:16.517
Amen.

25:20.121 --> 25:23.822
Ah, steak. How original.
Wh... where did you get this?

25:23.824 --> 25:26.492
Thanks.
Where did you get that suit?

25:26.494 --> 25:30.129
Actually, it's not a suit.
This is a feminine undergarment.

25:30.131 --> 25:32.631
- I took it from mother.
- Charles..

25:32.633 --> 25:35.167
Alain thinks Hitler is going to
invade Poland

25:35.169 --> 25:37.369
and the war is gonna spill
all over France.

25:37.371 --> 25:40.472
Hitler has zero chance
against France. He's bluffing.

25:40.474 --> 25:44.109
I almost wish he makes
that blunder so we destroy him.

25:44.111 --> 25:45.944
- Have you heard him talk?
- Ah!

25:45.946 --> 25:47.514
Talk, talk, talk, talk.

25:47.516 --> 25:50.616
Populist talk so that idiots
can rage with euphoria

25:50.618 --> 25:53.018
and feel better about their
miserable lives.

25:53.020 --> 25:54.787
I think Alain has a point

25:54.789 --> 25:57.890
and we should be ready
in case we have to leave.

25:57.892 --> 26:00.692
I left Poland to escape
anti-Semitism

26:00.694 --> 26:03.762
and now you're telling me
to prepare to leave again?

26:03.764 --> 26:05.030
No. No.

26:05.032 --> 26:07.666
Yeah, me too.
I... I can't just leave.

26:07.668 --> 26:09.968
Because of the children? Wow.

26:09.970 --> 26:12.604
The children? I'm helping
the children as much as I can

26:12.606 --> 26:14.206
but I'm working on my play,
okay?

26:14.208 --> 26:15.641
I'm upstairs painting
the backdrops myself.

26:15.643 --> 26:17.476
- Thank you very much.
- Yeah, I'm stupid.

26:17.478 --> 26:19.078
For a second I thought you had
started caring

26:19.080 --> 26:21.113
about someone
other than yourself.

26:21.115 --> 26:24.116
So.. Why would the children
be my responsibility?

26:24.118 --> 26:25.784
Maybe because
they are the only ones

26:25.786 --> 26:28.153
who don't consider your <i>art</i>

26:28.155 --> 26:29.990
completely ridiculous.

26:38.065 --> 26:42.768
There are 123 children
in that castle.

26:42.770 --> 26:46.105
Please, tell me, where... where
are we supposed to take them?

26:46.107 --> 26:47.975
Do whatever you want.

26:50.344 --> 26:52.911
You keep calling Marcel selfish.

26:52.913 --> 26:54.213
Yeah.

26:54.215 --> 26:55.647
But last I heard he's there

26:55.649 --> 26:56.949
helping children every day

26:56.951 --> 26:59.253
while you are theorizing
about Hitler.

27:06.193 --> 27:08.528
How long has it been?

27:08.530 --> 27:10.664
About a year
since they got here.

27:16.003 --> 27:18.837
Hello, Alain.

27:18.839 --> 27:20.975
Come on. Let's go.

27:23.444 --> 27:27.614
- Marcel!
- Oh, no. Incoming. Incoming.

27:27.616 --> 27:29.348
Ah!

27:29.350 --> 27:31.817
Oh, oh, please, help me.
Please, help me.

27:31.819 --> 27:35.287
Oh, okay. Whoa! W... whoa!

27:35.289 --> 27:37.956
Okay, thank you very much.
I hope you're happy now.

27:37.958 --> 27:39.258
- Marcel?
- Yes?

27:39.260 --> 27:41.827
- Can I tell you a secret?
- Yes. Quickly.

27:41.829 --> 27:44.096
Emma likes you.

27:44.098 --> 27:46.298
Okay. Yes. Oh, hello.

27:46.300 --> 27:48.400
- So, you like her, too?
- Oh, oh, yes.

27:48.402 --> 27:51.069
I... it's a great book. We are
talking about something else.

27:51.071 --> 27:53.438
Entirely different.

27:53.440 --> 27:57.176
I like every princess
in this castle. Okay?

27:57.178 --> 27:58.810
Maybe next time you want say it
a little louder.

27:58.812 --> 28:00.580
- I will.
- Broadcast it over the radio please.

28:00.582 --> 28:02.281
- <i>Bye, Marcel!</i>
- Goodbye.

28:02.283 --> 28:05.417
- Ah, Georges. Hello, Flore.
- Hello, Marcel.

28:05.419 --> 28:07.021
Alain!

28:09.757 --> 28:12.457
Hey! Georges!

28:12.459 --> 28:15.664
- Good to see you!
- Hello, Alain. Good to see you!

28:17.865 --> 28:20.265
<i>Tell me, what do you know?</i>

28:20.267 --> 28:22.569
No more than
what's on the radio.

28:22.571 --> 28:25.003
But we must prepare everyone
to move south.

28:25.005 --> 28:26.872
The children
are finally settled.

28:26.874 --> 28:30.342
It would be irresponsible not to
start looking for alternatives.

28:30.344 --> 28:32.477
What alternatives?
You've got another castle?

28:32.479 --> 28:35.414
Uh, no, no. Alain believes
having them all in one place

28:35.416 --> 28:37.849
is dangerous in itself. Right?

28:37.851 --> 28:39.787
I'm not sure I follow.

28:42.923 --> 28:46.858
Hitler's rise is empowering
the worst possible groups.

28:46.860 --> 28:49.428
Everybody knows Jewish children
are living here.

28:49.430 --> 28:51.330
You don't want this place
to become a target.

28:51.332 --> 28:53.666
I'm not going to bring them
more instability

28:53.668 --> 28:57.402
just because you suddenly feel
it may get dangerous.

28:57.404 --> 28:59.606
You are a mile away
from Nazi Germany

28:59.608 --> 29:01.406
where an extremely popular
leader is preparing

29:01.408 --> 29:04.142
<i>the most powerful army
in the history of Europe</i>

29:04.144 --> 29:06.646
to conquer a neighboring country

29:06.648 --> 29:09.783
while he blames
all possible evil on the Jews.

29:12.453 --> 29:15.420
Can I have one apple?

29:15.422 --> 29:16.725
Sure.

29:22.062 --> 29:24.198
- Be gentle.
- Yeah.

29:28.603 --> 29:32.371
I think all he is saying is
we should prepare for the worst.

29:32.373 --> 29:35.510
And he's right.
There is no other option.

29:37.646 --> 29:40.812
I also think I should get
started with their training.

29:40.814 --> 29:43.081
Training for what?

29:43.083 --> 29:45.484
They are children.

29:45.486 --> 29:47.622
We need to train them
to survive.

29:56.564 --> 29:58.700
- Nazis! Nazis!
- Nazis! Nazis!

30:00.702 --> 30:02.637
Hurry, Joseph!

30:30.699 --> 30:33.332
Juden?

30:33.334 --> 30:35.804
Juden? You maybe?

30:38.372 --> 30:40.606
Juden on the trees.

30:45.680 --> 30:48.349
- Don't do that!
- <i>Come down, Joseph!</i>

30:49.751 --> 30:52.117
- Ah!
- Yes.

30:52.119 --> 30:54.353
Listen.

30:54.355 --> 30:57.189
Your life and that of
all your friends

30:57.191 --> 30:59.324
will depend on your silence.

30:59.326 --> 31:00.760
We're not playing here.

31:00.762 --> 31:03.696
But Marcel is still funny,
Nazis are not.

31:07.569 --> 31:09.234
You see?

31:09.236 --> 31:11.838
Okay, everyone, come down.

31:11.840 --> 31:15.808
Now, have you seen
a squirrel hide?

31:15.810 --> 31:17.746
A squirrel?

31:26.186 --> 31:31.890
The squirrel does not find
a place to hide in the tree.

31:31.892 --> 31:34.993
No, the squirrel
finds a place to hide

31:34.995 --> 31:39.499
where she can become
a part of the tree.

31:39.501 --> 31:43.569
