1:11:35.395 --> 1:11:37.295
<i>I respect that, you see..</i>

1:11:37.297 --> 1:11:38.731
We won't be collaborators.

1:11:38.733 --> 1:11:41.432
All these other people,
no dignity.

1:11:41.434 --> 1:11:45.871
I would rather die like you
than live like them.

1:11:45.873 --> 1:11:48.276
<i>Don't say anything, please.</i>

1:11:51.444 --> 1:11:54.046
Don't say anything.

1:11:54.048 --> 1:11:57.315
<i>Don't say anything,
Emma, please.</i>

1:11:57.317 --> 1:12:01.120
<i>I don't care what he does.
I don't.</i>

1:12:01.122 --> 1:12:03.388
- <i>Please do not do that.</i>
- <i>Please, Emma.</i>

1:12:03.390 --> 1:12:05.191
- No, don't. Please
- <i>Emma, no. No, Emma, Emma.</i>

1:12:05.193 --> 1:12:07.693
- No. Please. Don't!
- Please, Emma. Emma, please!

1:12:07.695 --> 1:12:10.529
- No!
- Don't do that! Don't do that!

1:12:10.531 --> 1:12:12.332
No, don't!

1:12:20.440 --> 1:12:21.909
We have to go in.

1:12:23.578 --> 1:12:25.412
- We have to go in.
- No, no.

1:12:41.829 --> 1:12:44.397
- Klaus Barbie.
- Yeah. I see him.

1:13:27.074 --> 1:13:30.743
What you looking at?
It's fine, it's fine. It's fine.

1:13:37.151 --> 1:13:39.585
- It's her.
- Of course, it's her.

1:13:39.587 --> 1:13:41.153
Where's Mila?

1:13:41.155 --> 1:13:45.092
Nobody should bother you
as long as you're wearing this.

1:14:20.962 --> 1:14:22.363
Where is she?

1:14:24.999 --> 1:14:26.732
<i>She's going in
the train station.</i>

1:14:26.734 --> 1:14:28.000
Where the hell is Mila?

1:14:28.002 --> 1:14:29.969
I don't know.
Emma will tell us.

1:14:29.971 --> 1:14:32.004
They'll catch us
as soon as we approach her.

1:14:32.006 --> 1:14:33.471
Okay. Okay, listen to me.

1:14:33.473 --> 1:14:35.507
Okay, bring the guards
towards you and run.

1:14:35.509 --> 1:14:37.843
- I'm going in.
- It's too dangerous.

1:14:37.845 --> 1:14:39.479
So, let them kill me.

1:14:41.849 --> 1:14:44.085
Go. Be safe.

1:16:22.883 --> 1:16:24.218
What are you doing?

1:16:28.656 --> 1:16:31.156
<i>We must train and grow
with the Resistance.</i>

1:16:31.158 --> 1:16:33.325
We need to find guns.
We need to learn how to shoot.

1:16:33.327 --> 1:16:35.129
We need to learn explosives.

1:16:36.664 --> 1:16:38.597
They're not humans.

1:16:38.599 --> 1:16:41.001
No human would do that
to another.

1:16:47.842 --> 1:16:49.410
While you were there..

1:16:51.045 --> 1:16:53.412
...I... I filled myself
with hate

1:16:53.414 --> 1:16:56.882
and of course I did feel
an urge for revenge

1:16:56.884 --> 1:17:01.286
but... the more I thought
about it

1:17:01.288 --> 1:17:04.559
the only thing in my mind..

1:17:07.862 --> 1:17:10.698
...was why are we here..

1:17:12.266 --> 1:17:15.568
...fighting a war we can't win..

1:17:15.570 --> 1:17:17.769
...when we could be taking
orphan children

1:17:17.771 --> 1:17:22.009
to another country
before the Nazis get to them?

1:17:32.086 --> 1:17:34.419
We can't leave now.

1:17:34.421 --> 1:17:36.556
But what... what can we
truly accomplish?

1:17:36.558 --> 1:17:38.692
We can fight back.

1:17:42.296 --> 1:17:45.264
We found homes for the children.
Safe places.

1:17:45.266 --> 1:17:46.732
No place is safe for them

1:17:46.734 --> 1:17:50.102
as long as they're in a country
that's occupied by Nazis

1:17:50.104 --> 1:17:51.803
and the little fighting
that we can do...

1:17:51.805 --> 1:17:53.238
We can slow them down.

1:17:53.240 --> 1:17:55.676
We can make it impossible
for them in France.

1:18:04.318 --> 1:18:06.187
What is it the Nazis want?

1:18:10.791 --> 1:18:12.124
What?

1:18:12.126 --> 1:18:14.059
They don't care about
Klaus Barbie

1:18:14.061 --> 1:18:16.094
you know,
or a bunch of Gestapo slaves

1:18:16.096 --> 1:18:18.230
that we may kill,
if we are lucky...

1:18:18.232 --> 1:18:19.534
No, you are right.

1:18:20.868 --> 1:18:23.470
They care about killing us
like they killed her.

1:18:28.409 --> 1:18:30.344
So, what's the best way
to resist?

1:18:32.179 --> 1:18:34.780
It's not to kill them.

1:18:34.782 --> 1:18:37.349
They're ready to die!

1:18:37.351 --> 1:18:38.651
If you want to resist

1:18:38.653 --> 1:18:42.389
we have to make sure
more Jews survive.

1:18:45.660 --> 1:18:48.128
How can you not want to go
and murder him?

1:18:49.196 --> 1:18:50.929
Of course,
I want to murder Barbie.

1:18:50.931 --> 1:18:55.467
I want Hitler to die as well,
but we can't kill all the Nazis.

1:18:55.469 --> 1:18:57.805
- We can kill some.
- Mm-hmm.

1:19:00.908 --> 1:19:02.776
Or you can save some lives.

1:19:04.679 --> 1:19:09.848
And maybe one day those Nazis
will be captured..

1:19:09.850 --> 1:19:14.388
...while the kids we saved
go on and... and form families.

1:19:21.128 --> 1:19:23.397
What about those
who already died?

1:19:25.634 --> 1:19:27.835
What do you think
they would want us to do?

1:19:29.504 --> 1:19:33.506
Risk our lives
to take revenge on their killers

1:19:33.508 --> 1:19:36.511
or do it to help
their orphans survive?

1:19:52.092 --> 1:19:53.728
We have to save the children.

1:19:56.564 --> 1:19:57.732
We will.

1:20:05.939 --> 1:20:08.876
<i>Germany, Poland.</i>

1:20:10.077 --> 1:20:12.110
<i>All over Europe.</i>

1:20:12.112 --> 1:20:16.150
<i>We're gonna be receiving
50 to 100 orphans a month.</i>

1:20:17.686 --> 1:20:22.356
Listen, we want to help you
take them out of France.

1:20:23.891 --> 1:20:25.824
Take them where?

1:20:25.826 --> 1:20:28.960
Even the allies have reached
their cap on refugees.

1:20:28.962 --> 1:20:31.496
What about Switzerland?

1:20:31.498 --> 1:20:35.336
You plan to take children
across snow covered mountains?

1:20:37.539 --> 1:20:39.373
<i>At least it's safe here.</i>

1:20:40.174 --> 1:20:41.507
They are not safe.

1:20:41.509 --> 1:20:43.643
If they are captured in the Alps

1:20:43.645 --> 1:20:46.845
we'll not only have to carry
the responsibility of a disgrace

1:20:46.847 --> 1:20:49.448
but we will also lose the
credibility and the funding

1:20:49.450 --> 1:20:51.686
we need to take care
of the rest of the children.

1:20:53.087 --> 1:20:54.723
They are not safe.

1:20:58.025 --> 1:21:00.392
Georges, listen..

1:21:00.394 --> 1:21:03.462
...let us take a small group..

1:21:03.464 --> 1:21:05.834
...to see if we can get across
the border.

1:21:07.702 --> 1:21:09.336
<i>Please.</i>

1:21:26.487 --> 1:21:28.222
Shh, shh.
Shh. Shh.

1:21:33.327 --> 1:21:35.394
- No, Marcel. What..
- Shh, shh.

1:21:35.396 --> 1:21:38.332
- <i>Where have you been?</i>
- Shh, shh. Shh.

1:22:07.161 --> 1:22:08.393
<i>Go on, kids.</i>

1:22:08.395 --> 1:22:11.196
Do what Marcel and Emma
and Alain say

1:22:11.198 --> 1:22:13.999
and I promise
everything will be fine.

1:22:14.001 --> 1:22:15.668
Thank you.

1:22:15.670 --> 1:22:17.839
Thank you for saving our lives.

1:22:23.511 --> 1:22:25.778
- Thank you!
- <i>Go, go, go, go, go!</i>

1:22:25.780 --> 1:22:28.949
Go, go.
Let's go now. Out. Go out.

1:22:30.150 --> 1:22:32.451
Alright. Let's go.

1:22:32.453 --> 1:22:34.286
- Alright.
- Come on, kids. Let's go.

1:22:34.288 --> 1:22:35.723
Come on.

1:22:36.825 --> 1:22:38.793
- There you go. Here.
- Goodbye.

1:22:40.961 --> 1:22:42.227
<i>Go, son.</i>

1:22:42.229 --> 1:22:44.229
You and mother need to
get out of Europe as well.

1:22:44.231 --> 1:22:46.801
Go! Go!

1:23:06.821 --> 1:23:10.658
I understand there's a meeting
about visas for foreign Jews.

1:23:29.811 --> 1:23:31.378
No, I..

1:24:06.280 --> 1:24:10.482
The least guarded place at the
border is the end of this ridge.

1:24:10.484 --> 1:24:14.587
We're gonna go through this forest,
which is supposed to be easier.

1:24:14.589 --> 1:24:17.255
That will take us to a path
leading down the ridge

1:24:17.257 --> 1:24:20.494
down this mountain... to Geneva.

1:24:22.931 --> 1:24:25.430
<i>And there's a... a trail
down the ridge?</i>

1:24:25.432 --> 1:24:26.668
<i>Yes.</i>

1:24:29.369 --> 1:24:32.874
Emma... you can tell me
about Mila.

1:24:34.676 --> 1:24:37.779
I mean, I lost my father
and my mother.

1:24:43.017 --> 1:24:45.620
People always feel sorry
for those who die.

1:24:47.055 --> 1:24:49.489
They should feel worse
for those who live.

1:24:53.260 --> 1:24:57.530
There... there are lots of
beautiful things in life.

1:24:57.532 --> 1:24:59.499
If you could share it.

1:25:04.304 --> 1:25:06.674
Mila is no longer with us..

1:25:08.843 --> 1:25:13.047
...but we are here to make sure
that you are all safe.

1:25:14.682 --> 1:25:16.882
Mila wouldn't want me to be sad.

1:25:16.884 --> 1:25:19.821
And I'm sure your parents
would want you to be happy.

1:25:24.659 --> 1:25:26.493
We were never sad.

1:25:31.498 --> 1:25:33.067
Come here.

1:25:46.047 --> 1:25:48.082
I didn't know
there was a stop in Lyon.

1:25:49.617 --> 1:25:51.552
It should be only a minute.

1:26:14.008 --> 1:26:15.041
He's here!

1:26:15.043 --> 1:26:16.408
Who is?

1:26:16.410 --> 1:26:17.910
Barbie.

1:26:17.912 --> 1:26:18.946
<i>No.</i>

1:26:20.081 --> 1:26:22.748
- I have to jump.
- No, no, no. No.

1:26:22.750 --> 1:26:24.852
Okay, singing position.

1:26:37.431 --> 1:26:39.865
If he recognizes me,
he's gonna kill them all!

1:26:39.867 --> 1:26:42.103
We cannot just leave you. Here!

1:26:43.403 --> 1:26:46.605
Oh, okay, go. Go, go, go.
Come, come, come.

1:26:46.607 --> 1:26:48.843
Lock the door.
Lock the door.

