Do you hear me?

1:48:36.384 --> 1:48:40.152
Emma, listen to me!
It's okay. Are you okay?

1:48:40.154 --> 1:48:42.354
The kids are all here.
It's okay.

1:48:42.356 --> 1:48:45.624
It's okay. Please, Emma.
Please, talk to me.

1:48:45.626 --> 1:48:47.962
Do you hear me?
Do you hear me?

1:48:48.863 --> 1:48:50.364
Emma?

1:48:52.566 --> 1:48:53.901
Emma, talk to me!

1:48:56.904 --> 1:48:58.572
Emma!

1:49:47.321 --> 1:49:48.523
Oh!

1:49:50.925 --> 1:49:52.093
Do you need help?

1:49:53.461 --> 1:49:55.160
Help? Wh..

1:49:55.162 --> 1:49:56.728
Where... where are we?

1:49:56.730 --> 1:49:58.197
In the Alps.

1:49:58.199 --> 1:50:00.668
Yes... yes,
but, but what... what country?

1:50:02.470 --> 1:50:05.005
You came all the way
from France?

1:50:05.973 --> 1:50:07.141
Fra..

1:50:08.142 --> 1:50:10.375
Switzerland?

1:50:10.377 --> 1:50:11.977
Yes, we are.

1:50:21.689 --> 1:50:24.723
We made it!

1:50:24.725 --> 1:50:26.660
We made it!

1:50:37.004 --> 1:50:38.706
Look at that!

1:50:41.108 --> 1:50:42.774
Let's go! Let's go!

1:51:30.391 --> 1:51:33.192
<i>He risked his life many times
by crossing the Alps</i>

1:51:33.194 --> 1:51:35.496
<i>to take orphans to safety.</i>

1:51:37.932 --> 1:51:42.134
He is personally
directly responsible

1:51:42.136 --> 1:51:44.271
for saving hundreds of children.

1:51:45.839 --> 1:51:49.376
And indirectly responsible
for saving thousands.

1:51:52.046 --> 1:51:55.015
He's now
one of our liaison officers.

1:51:56.350 --> 1:51:58.750
But he's also an actor

1:51:58.752 --> 1:52:01.086
and you are about to see his

1:52:01.088 --> 1:52:04.356
first official
public performance.

1:52:04.358 --> 1:52:09.394
Soldiers, remember his name..

1:52:09.396 --> 1:52:11.533
...because he will
never forget you..

1:52:13.901 --> 1:52:15.704
Marcel Marceau!
